        <abstract> 
<p>In his reply to [<hi rend="doubleUnderline">7227</hi>] CD questions the significance of the supposed likeness of the bee, spider, and fly orchids to their presumed namesakes.</p> 
            <p>He thinks that the beauty of shells is altogether incidental and of no use to the animals.</p>
        </abstract>
